description:
&lt;p&gt;Priory Hospital Enfield is set within the grounds of an old Chapel. It is a two minute walk from Edmonton Green train station (overground) and is 0.8 miles from the A10. Walking through the relaxed grounds does not give the impression that it is set in Central London and this promotes the safe and therapeutic environment which Priory Hospital Enfield has developed and established to ensure patients receive the best care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospital encourages a Multi-Disciplinary approach to delivering care, and this allows patients to receive a comprehensive care pathway during their admission to the hospital. The therapies provided for Service Users can be tailored to meet their specific needs and there are opportunities for all staff to receive extra training in the therapies being delivered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospital provides three service lines across four wards:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acute mental illness (12 bedded mixed sex ward)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2 Medium Secure male wards (1 sixteen bedded acute and 1 fifteen bedded recovery)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 Low Secure male ward&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospital has a flexible approach to service delivery, and this is seen through the development of a new acute ward which is due to be open in Spring 2020. This is an opportunity to join an evolving service which puts patient care as our main priority!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ready for the recognition&lt;em&gt;and rewards you deserve?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;We don’t just talk about putting employees first. We know that Priory wouldn’t exist without their combined energy, expertise and effort. So we invest heavily in training, provide first-class support, promote collaborative teamwork and give everyone on our team the opportunities and resources to achieve their full potential. All roles will be subject to a successful disclosure at an appropriate level from the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS). Priory Group will cover the cost of a DBS check for all successful applicants&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role: Role responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To accept personal and shared responsibility for the maintenance of quality nursing care, for all patients as part of a multidisciplinary team approach within a forensic setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To work as a Primary Nurse/Care Coordinator for an identified group of patients whilst consistently working within the clinical governance framework.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to develop and progress across the Staff Nurse grading through a distinct career pathway.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful as a RMN, you’ll need:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A RMN or RNLD qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven ability to co-ordinate care, prioritise tasks and manage Health &amp; Safety issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The drive to learn and develop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to patient-centred care and to values-based and evidence-based practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A flexible, positive, team-orientated approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your expertise and hard work, we offer a wide range of benefits including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25 days’ annual leave plus 8 bank holidays increasing to 30 days plus bank holidays with length of service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extra Service Annual leave awards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career development – progress across the Staff Nurse grading is via a distinct career path&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An employee assistance programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals/refreshments when on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free car parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NMC Payment in full&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Payment into the pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPD top up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Donation to a charity of their choice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£3,000 Welcome Bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
